      <li><a href="https://twitter.com/amandahess" class="follow twitter" data-show-count="true" data-lang="en"></a></li>
    
    
      
      <li><a href="http://www.slate.com/authors.amanda_hess.slateplus.html" class="follow slateplus"></a></li>
      
    
      <li><a href="http://picks.slate.com/authors/amanda-hess" class="follow picks"></a></li>
    
      
        <li style="display:none"><a href="https://plus.google.com/118331020221652244544/"></a></li>
      
    </ul>
</section> <!-- /.about-the-author -->


<div class="text-2 text parbase section">

<p>Pegging in pop culture is typically presented as emasculating and painful for the man (<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B006GLPA8O/?tag=slatmaga-20"><em>Entourage</em></a><em>, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B00008WJBD/?tag=slatmaga-20">Arliss</a>,&nbsp;</em>the 2006 thriller<em> </em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B001X9PSF4/?tag=slatmaga-20"><em>One Way</em></a>), but <em>Broad City</em> reframes the sexual practice as empowering for the woman: When Abbi calls bestie Ilana for advice, Ilana performs a celebratory dance, announces it a &ldquo;dream come true,&rdquo; and celebrates the prospect of Abbi penetrating Jeremy&rsquo;s &ldquo;hairy, adorable little butthole&rdquo; and &ldquo;plowing it like a queen.&rdquo; Emboldened, Abbi straps on the dildo, and triumphs. In a blissful morning-after scene, Jeremy kisses Abbi goodbye before he departs for his volunteer gig teaching woodworking to underprivileged children. She swoons. (The scene reminded me of a feature I wrote for <em>Playboy </em>a couple of years ago about <a href="http://playboysfw.kinja.com/tongue-in-cheek-the-men-who-want-this-sex-act-arent-1467464439">guys who are into butt stuff</a>; one man told me that he views the experience of being penetrated as a kind of masculine badge of honor because &ldquo;you can talk about being tough and fearless and open and sensitive, but nothing puts that to the test like allowing&mdash;and enjoying&mdash;foreign objects in the out door.&rdquo;) Later, when Ilana&rsquo;s family finds out about the incident, the show gets servicey: Ilana&rsquo;s parents wonder aloud whether pegging is a gay thing, and her brother replies: &ldquo;No. How would I put a dildo on top of my dick? Both gay and straight men enjoy prostate stimulation.&rdquo;</p>


</div>

<div class="brightcovevideosingle section">







<!-- Start of Brightcove Player -->
